ai.grakn.engine.tasks.storage

Class TaskStateZookeeperStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • ai.grakn.engine.tasks.storage.TaskStateZookeeperStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TaskStateStorage

    public class TaskStateZookeeperStore
extends Object
implements TaskStateStorage

    Manages the state of background BackgroundTask in a synchronized manner withing a cluster. This means that all updates must be performed by acquiring a distributed mutex so that no concurrent writes are possible.

        public Boolean updateState(TaskState task)

                               String taskClassName,
                               String createdBy,
                               EngineID engineRunningOn,

                               int offset)
        This implementation will fetch all of the tasks from zookeeper and then filer them out. ZK stores tasks by ID, so at the moment there is no more efficient way to search within the storage itself.
        Specified by:

        createdBy - String containing created by. See TaskState.
